The paper discusses a new framework for information hiding security, which is related to cryptography and information theory (cs.CR, cs.IT). It also presents a novel data hiding scheme that involves multimedia (cs.MM) and image processing (cs.CV) techniques. The paper also discusses the evaluation of chaos-security properties, which is related to signal processing and system identification (cs.SI).
